    "explanation": "<p>The rate of $\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{N}} 1$ reaction is directly proportional to the stability of carbocation.</p>\n<p>Among the given options, (b) has most stable carbocation.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh7z7rlf/9d4406b6-ff83-4c8f-9571-11f69c6c6307/49162c30-b290-11f0-a024-8d037bc62597/file-jaoe38c1mh7z7rlg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh7z7rlf/9d4406b6-ff83-4c8f-9571-11f69c6c6307/49162c30-b290-11f0-a024-8d037bc62597/file-jaoe38c1mh7z7rlg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2025 Chemistry - Halogen Derivatives Question 2 English Explanation\">",
